Parliament, Tuesday, 27 February 2018 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow hold a hearing with the South African Police Service on irregular, fruitless and wasteful expenditure. The hearing will also look into the Forensic Data Analysts (FDA) contract and other contracts. Details of the meeting: Date: Wednesday, 28 February 2018
	Time: 09:00
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI. For media enquiries, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8062
	Cell: 081 377 0686
